<br>
Be careful when buying a belt, because even though it says 2 slots freed, it might be more or less. Scroll down to the description of the belt, and you'll see the actual number freed. The same goes for NCU components. It might be called 8NCU, but it can be more or less than that. It depends on the quality level.<br>
<br>
The skill needed is Computer Literacy, and that is all. You can get a cheap general CompLit buff which boosts your skill by 20, but other that that you have to spend IP's.<br>
<br>
Regarding implants, that's really an individual thing. I'm level 43, and only recently completed my set of QL50 implants. Some people will tell you that you should be getting QL70 implants at that level, but personally, I'm not one who pushes my options to the limit. But that's just me. Before that I only had what I found on missions, which wasn't much use. Whatever you do, be aware that implant require A LOT of money to gather, so plan a bit over your current stats, since they will probably be raised before you collect your set <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
There are plenty of tools on the net that will help you assemble implants. AONanoNanny evem tells you how much Treatment skill and basic stat level is needed to install a particular implant.<br>
<br>
